        <div class="pcard-stars">
          <span class="stars">&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;&#9734;</span>
          <span class="rating-val">4.2</span>
          <span class="review-ct">(5,400 reviews)</span>
        </div>
        <div class="pcard-specs">
          <div class="pcard-spec"><strong>Key Ingredients</strong><span>L-Theanine, Alpha-GPC, B-Vitamins</span></div>
          <div class="pcard-spec"><strong>Caffeine</strong><span>None</span></div>
          <div class="pcard-spec"><strong>Formulation</strong><span>Pectin-based, Berry flavor</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="pcard-price">
          <span class="price">$16.99</span>
          <span class="per-serv">$0.57/day (30ct)</span>
        </div>
        <div class="pcard-ctas">
          <a href="https://www.amazon.com/s?k=Olly+Ultra+Focus+Gummies&tag=gummyguide-20" class="btn-cta" target="_blank" rel="nofollow sponsored noopener">Check Price on Amazon</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p>Olly Ultra Focus delivers L-theanine and alpha-GPC — two of the best-evidenced nootropic ingredients — at a mainstream price point. The L-theanine provides acute focus support within 30-40 minutes, while alpha-GPC supports acetylcholine synthesis for memory and learning. For the full focus gummy comparison, see our <a href="/trending/focus-gummies/">best focus gummies</a> guide.</p>

    <div class="callout">
      The most effective nootropic stack for daily cognitive performance combines an acute nootropic (L-theanine for immediate focus) with a cumulative nootropic (lion's mane for long-term neuroplasticity). Take L-theanine before demanding cognitive tasks and lion's mane daily at any time. Add 100mg caffeine from coffee for the well-documented L-theanine + caffeine synergy.
      <cite>— James Rodriguez, CPT, CSCS</cite>
    </div>

    <div class="warn-box">
      <span class="warn-box-ico">&#9888;</span>
      <p><strong>Beware of proprietary blends.</strong> Many nootropic gummies list impressive ingredient names but hide the actual amounts behind "proprietary blend" labeling. A formula listing "500mg Focus Blend (L-theanine, alpha-GPC, bacopa)" could contain 490mg of cheap L-theanine and 5mg each of the expensive ingredients. Always choose products that disclose individual ingredient doses so you can verify clinically relevant amounts.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- VERDICT -->
    <div class="verdict">
      <h3>The Bottom Line on Nootropic Gummies</h3>
      <p><strong>For immediate focus:</strong> L-theanine at 200mg is the most evidence-backed acute nootropic. Effects within 30-40 minutes. Pairs synergistically with coffee.</p>
      <p><strong>For long-term brain health:</strong> Lion's mane at 500-1000mg daily stimulates NGF for progressive cognitive improvement. Give it 4-8 weeks.</p>
      <p><strong>For the best of both:</strong> Combine a L-theanine gummy (or Alpha Brain) for daily focus with a lion's mane gummy for cumulative neuroplasticity. This dual approach provides immediate and compounding cognitive benefits.</p>
      <p><strong>Avoid:</strong> Products with proprietary blends, undisclosed doses, or ingredients with no published human clinical data. The best nootropic gummies are transparent about what they contain and at what dosage.</p>
    </div>

