    <!-- FAQ -->
    <section class="faq-sec">
      <h2>Nootropic Gummies — Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <details class="fq"><summary>What are nootropic gummies?</summary><p>Gummy supplements containing ingredients that enhance cognitive function — focus, memory, processing speed. Key ingredients include L-theanine, lion's mane, alpha-GPC, and bacopa monnieri. They provide a convenient, pleasant-tasting format for daily brain support.</p></details>
      <details class="fq"><summary>Do nootropic gummies actually work?</summary><p>Yes, when they contain clinically dosed ingredients. L-theanine (200mg) produces measurable alpha brain waves within 30-40 min. Lion's mane (500mg+) improves cognition over 8-16 weeks. Avoid products with proprietary blends hiding actual amounts.</p></details>
      <details class="fq"><summary>What is the best nootropic for focus?</summary><p>L-theanine (200mg) for immediate focus. Lion's mane (500-1000mg) for long-term cognitive enhancement. Combining both provides immediate and cumulative benefits. Add 100mg caffeine for the documented L-theanine + caffeine synergy.</p></details>
      <details class="fq"><summary>Are nootropic gummies safe for daily use?</summary><p>L-theanine, lion's mane, and B-vitamins have excellent safety profiles for daily use in clinical trials. Alpha-GPC and bacopa are well-tolerated at standard doses. Stimulant-containing products should be used more cautiously.</p></details>
      <details class="fq"><summary>How long do nootropic gummies take to work?</summary><p>L-theanine: 30-40 minutes (acute). Alpha-GPC: 1-2 hours (acute). Lion's mane: 2-4 weeks (cumulative). Bacopa: 4-8 weeks (cumulative). Different ingredients work on different timescales.</p></details>
      <details class="fq"><summary>Can I take nootropic gummies with coffee?</summary><p>Yes. L-theanine synergizes with caffeine, smoothing jitters while preserving alertness. A 2008 study confirmed improved attention from the combination. Optimal ratio: 200mg L-theanine with 100mg caffeine (one cup).</p></details>
      <details class="fq"><summary>What is the difference between nootropic and focus gummies?</summary><p>Largely interchangeable. "Nootropic" implies broader cognitive scope (memory + focus + neuroprotection). "Focus" emphasizes acute attention. Ingredient profiles overlap significantly — both commonly use L-theanine, lion's mane, and B-vitamins.</p></details>
      <details class="fq"><summary>Are nootropic gummies better than capsules?</summary><p>Same bioavailability for most ingredients. Gummies win on taste, compliance, and convenience. Capsules win on dose density (more active ingredient per unit). For standard doses, gummies are equally effective.</p></details>
